de-chats-in-the-turing-way","implicit":true,"key":"NkGCSxFI1F"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":30,"column":1},"end":{"line":31,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In ","position":{"start":{"line":30,"column":1},"end":{"line":30,"column":1}},"key":"Rn0ZTvt27E"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":30,"column":1},"end":{"line":30,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The Turing Way","position":{"start":{"line":30,"column":1},"end":{"line":30,"column":1}},"key":"IJc7nwidrs"}],"key":"vTLfYtO2Ph"},{"type":"text","value":", we imagine Fireside Chats as conversations among friends and colleagues taking place around a warm inviting fireplace.\nThrough the Fireside Chat series in ","position":{"start":{"line":30,"column":1},"end":{"line":30,"column":1}},"key":"AjlKJsJWw3"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":30,"column":1},"end":{"line":30,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The Turing Way","position":{"start":{"line":30,"column":1},"end":{"line":30,"column":1}},"key":"ELUBRRNh4R"}],"key":"VXRLT5hKpz"},{"type":"text","value":", we want to build an intentional space to gather, facilitate important conversations and establish cross-community collaborations.","position":{"start":{"line":30,"column":1},"end":{"line":30,"column":1}},"key":"mgNvl8dOG0"}],"key":"JISYgtM4Ia"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":33,"column":1},"end":{"line":36,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Different stakeholders in open research and grassroots communities have a shared mission of making scientific knowledge freely available for public access and for the benefit of society.\nHowever, most of these communities operate independently of other initiatives, either lacking the capacity to build meaningful collaboration or competing for limited resources.\nThis often results in scientific outputs that most users can find, but not access, or build upon in their local contexts.\nOpen discussions and spaces